						Shemirat Enayim provides educational information and resources about internet safety, content filtering,
						and parental controls ("the Service"). The Site offers guides, tutorials, and recommendations for
						protecting individuals and families from inappropriate online content.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section class="legal-section">
					<h2>3. Educational Purpose Only</h2>
					<p>
						All content on this Site is provided for educational and informational purposes only. The information
						is not intended as professional advice and should not be relied upon as such. You should:
					</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Verify all information independently before implementing any solutions</li>
						<li>Consult with qualified professionals for specific technical or legal advice</li>
						<li>Test all filtering solutions in your own environment</li>
						<li>Understand that technology and platforms change frequently</li>
					</ul>
				</section>

				<section class="legal-section">
					<h2>4. No Warranties</h2>
					<p>
						This Site and all content are provided "as is" without warranty of any kind, either express or implied,
						including but not limited to:
					</p>
					<ul>
						<li><strong>Accuracy:</strong> We strive for accuracy but cannot guarantee that all information is current or complete</li>
						<li><strong>Effectiveness:</strong> We do not warrant that any filtering solution will be 100% effective</li>
						<li><strong>Availability:</strong> We do not guarantee uninterrupted access to the Site</li>
						<li><strong>Fitness:</strong> We do not warrant that solutions are suitable for your specific needs</li>
					</ul>
				</section>

				<section class="legal-section">
					<h2>5. Limitation of Liability</h2>
					<p>
						To the fullest extent permitted by law, Shemirat Enayim and its operators shall not be liable for:
					</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Any damages arising from use or inability to use the Site or its content</li>
						<li>Failure of any recommended filtering solution or software</li>
						<li>Access to inappropriate content despite implementing recommended solutions</li>
						<li>Technical issues, data loss, or security breaches related to recommended solutions</li>
						<li>Actions taken based on information provided on this Site</li>
					</ul>
					<p>
						You acknowledge that no filtering solution is perfect and that determined users may find ways to
						bypass protections. Ultimate responsibility for online safety remains with parents, guardians, and users.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section class="legal-section">
					<h2>6. Third-Party Services and Links</h2>
					<p>
						This Site contains references to and links to third-party products, services, and websites. Please note:
					</p>
					<ul>
						<li>We are not affiliated with or endorsed by any third-party vendor unless explicitly stated</li>
						<li>We do not control third-party websites and are not responsible for their content or practices</li>
						<li>Links do not constitute endorsements or guarantees of effectiveness</li>
						<li>Pricing, features, and availability of third-party services may change without notice</li>
						<li>You should review terms of service and privacy policies of all third-party services you use</li>
					</ul>
				</section>

				<section class="legal-section">
					<h2>7. Vendor Neutrality</h2>
					<p>
						Shemirat Enayim maintains independence from filtering software vendors and manufacturers. Our
						recommendations are based on features, usability, and general effectiveness, not commercial relationships.
						We receive no compensation from any vendors mentioned on this Site.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section class="legal-section">
					<h2>8. Accuracy and Currency</h2>
					<p>
						Technology platforms frequently update their interfaces, features, and settings. While we strive to
						keep our guides current:
					</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Screenshots and specific menu paths may not reflect the latest platform versions</li>
						<li>Features mentioned may be added, removed, or changed by vendors</li>
						<li>Pricing information may be outdated</li>
						<li>Some solutions may no longer be available</li>
					</ul>
					<p>
						Always verify information directly with the software vendor or platform before proceeding.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section class="legal-section">
					<h2>9. User Responsibilities</h2>
					<p>
						When using this Site and implementing recommended solutions, you agree to:
					</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Comply with all applicable laws and regulations</li>
						<li>Respect intellectual property rights of third parties</li>
						<li>Not use the Site to harm minors or facilitate illegal activities</li>
						<li>Not attempt to circumvent security measures or access restricted areas of the Site</li>
						<li>Take responsibility for your own internet safety decisions</li>
					</ul>
				</section>

				<section class="legal-section">
					<h2>10. Privacy and Data Collection</h2>
					<p>
						Our collection and use of personal information is governed by our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
						By using this Site, you consent to the practices described in that policy.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section class="legal-section">
